t27 Transfer of Power . Films Officers in the British Coal Industry -- t28 Saudi Arabia's John Ford? . Robert Yarnall Richie, Desert Venture and Ephemeral Authorship in Industrial Film -- t29 Sounds Industrial . Understanding the Contribution of Music and Sound in Industrial Films -- t30 Creative Films for Creative Corporations . Music and Musicians in Experimental Italian Industrial Films -- tIndices0 aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aWhat unleashed the forces of global capitalism which continue to shape the world that we live in? Economists and economic historians variously point to innovations in logistics and trade, the emergence of a new set of business-friendly values and the emergence of new forms of applied knowledge in early modernity to solve this riddle. This book focuses on the moving image as a factor of economic development. In a series of in-depth cases studies at the intersection of film and media studies, science and technology studies and economic and social history, Films That Work Harder: The Circulations of Industrial Film presents an in-depth, global perspective on the dynamic relationship between film, industrial organization and economic development. Bringing together new research from leading scholars from Europe, Asia, Australia and North America, this book combines the state of the art in the field with an agenda for a future research.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aFilm Studies. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 4aMedia Studies. 4aScience and Technology. 7aART / Film & Video.2bisacsh  aIndustrial film, non-theatrical film, film studies and science and technology studies, economic history,